title: DOGE staffers who have been detailed to NASA

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

In a sworn declaration by Deputy Administrator Florence Felix-Watson in AFL-CIO vs. Social Security Administration (source https://storage.courtlistener.com/recap/gov.uscourts.dcd.277150/gov.uscourts.dcd.277150.53.1.pdf), she testified that on Feb. 18, 2025 they "began onboarding and training Employee 2, Senior Advisor (Program Specialist AD-0301-00). He is in the process of being detailed from National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) to SSA."

This FOIA is to request details on who that person is and any other relevant details of that detailing arrangement (like a memorandum of understanding or coordination emails). If possible, I would like to request whatever onboarding details for that employee at NASA, including if they had a signed SF-61. Thank you.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jacob Harris

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

I would like all responsive documents for the Fighting Marine "Victor Krulak" or Victor H. Krulak in the years 1961 to 1968.  I am especially interested in any documents relating to the organization "SACSA".  If the response documents are too voluminous, please use the filter "SACSA" as a way of reducing the responsive documents.  I am also interested in any documents which include the name Kennedy.  Thank you very much.  George Webb Sweigert

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

George Webb Sweigert
